Preheat your oven to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} into 3cm chunks (no need to peel). Pop onto a large #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf for ~{20%minutes} - you'll roast them for longer once
you've crushed them.

Meanwhile, roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1%bunch}(roughly chopped, stalks and all).

In a #small bowl{}, combine the @panko breadcrumbs{10%grams}, @salt{1/4%tsp} and
@oil for the breadcrumbs{1/2%tbsp} and half the parsley. Set the herby crumb aside.

Trim the @Brussels sprouts{200%grams} and quarter through the root.

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Lay the @salmon fillets{2}, skin-side down, onto a large, lined baking tray and spread half the
@mayonnaise{64%grams} over the top of the fillets.

Top with the herby crumbs, pressing them down to ensure they stick. Set aside.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw fish.

When the potatoes have cooked for ~{20%minutes}, remove them from the oven. Use the bottom of a
#bowl{} or pan to lightly crush each potato.

Drizzle the smashed potatoes with more oil and sprinkle over the
@grated hard Italian style cheese{20%grams}. Return to the middle shelf of your oven until crispy
and golden, ~{10-15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pop the salmon on the top shelf to bake until the crumbs are golden and the salmon is
cooked through, ~{10-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The fish is cooked when opaque in the middle.

While everything bakes, heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the sprouts to the pan and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir-fry until
starting to brown, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Stir in the garlic, then turn the heat down to medium and cook for ~{1%minute} more. Add the
@dried cranberries{30%grams} and a splash of @water{} and immediately cover with a #lid{} or some
#foil{}.

Allow to cook until the sprouts are tender, ~{4-5%minutes}, then remove from the heat. Stir
through the @balsamic glaze{12%ml} and @pine nuts{15%grams}.

When everything's ready, share the herb crusted salmon, smashed potatoes and cranberry sprouts
between your plates.

Sprinkle the remaining parsley over the potatoes and serve with the remaining mayo on the side.

Enjoy!